{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3161061,"name":"Victoria","username":"vickitine","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/vickitine/{size}/180654_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-09T18:54:10.622Z","cooked":"<p>Our team is having an issue with importing and configuring the limit switch on our robot. This is a coding issue not hardware and the code itself quitting unexpectedly. We know it’s quitting because of the limit sensor config as when we take it out the code works fine. We are just confused on how to properly implement the limit switch. The github with our full code is here: <a href="https://github.com/vickitine404/FixingSpin" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Github</a> ; itll all be the in the elevator command and subsystem files. Here is what our subsystem code looks like currently that’s giving us the errors.</p>
<p>package frc.robot.subsystems;</p>
<p>import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.DigitalInput;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Encoder;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.smartdashboard.SmartDashboard;<br>
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.SubsystemBase;</p>
<p>import com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.InvertType;<br>
import com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.TalonFXControlMode;<br>
//import com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.can.TalonFX;<br>
import com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.can.WPI_TalonFX;</p>
<p>public class Elevator extends SubsystemBase {<br>
private final WPI_TalonFX  masterMotor;<br>
private final WPI_TalonFX  followerMotor;<br>
private final Encoder encoder;<br>
public final DigitalInput limitSensor;<br>
DigitalInput limitSensorTop = new DigitalInput(1);</p>
<pre><code>public int upperLimit;
//public int bottomLimit;
//public boolean isTopLimitSwitchTriggered = false;


public Elevator(WPI_TalonFX masterMotor, WPI_TalonFX followerMotor, int channelA, int channelB, int limitChannel ) {
    this.masterMotor = masterMotor;
    this.followerMotor = followerMotor;
    this.encoder = new Encoder(channelA, channelB);
    this.limitSensor = new DigitalInput(limitChannel);
}

public void defineLimits(){

}

public void setMotors(double speed) {

    masterMotor.set(TalonFXControlMode.PercentOutput, speed);
    followerMotor.follow(masterMotor);
    followerMotor.setInverted(InvertType.FollowMaster);
    SmartDashboard.putNumber("encoder", encoder.get());

}
</code></pre>
