<p>It looks to me as if both <code>limitSensorTop</code> and <code>limitSensor</code> are <code>DigitalInput</code>s on channel 1.  Is that intended?</p>
<p>This code belongs in the constructor, not in <code>setMotors</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">        followerMotor.follow(masterMotor);
        followerMotor.setInverted(InvertType.FollowMaster);
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2023-03-09T19:08:16.625Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":29.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":429595,"topic_slug":"limit-sensor-crashing-code","display_username":"Gavin Matthews","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/basic-programming/reading-stacktraces.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Reading Stacktraces — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38743,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)"},"post_url":"/t/limit-sensor-crashing-code/429595/2","custom_user_title":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3161077,"name":"Victoria","username":"vickitine","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/vickitine/{size}/180654_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-09T19:17:57.871Z","cooked":"<p>The lines that are giving the error are as followed:</p>
<p>RobotContainer file: private final Elevator s_Elevator = new Elevator(new WPI_TalonFX(Constants.Elevator.leftElevator), new WPI_TalonFX(Constants.Elevator.rightElevator), 8, 9,1);<br>
Command file: this.limitSensor = new DigitalInput(limitChannel);</p>
<p>We have our limit switch set up to pwm port 1 right now, which is why we set them to 1. I’ve never set a limit switch up before so the channel could be part of the problem. We never had a problem when we have just the motors, although I can see now it being an issue when adding other stuff in the file.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2023-03-09T19:17:57.871Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":13.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":429595,"topic_slug":"limit-sensor-crashing-code","display_username":"Victoria","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":38743,"username":"bovlb","name":"Gavin Matthews","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":55902,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/limit-sensor-crashing-code/429595/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3161081,"name":"","username":"cmarley","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cmarley/{size}/121111_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-09T19:19:35.696Z","cooked":"<p>Limit switches need to be inserted into a DIO port, and you can’t allocate the same space (channel) for two limit switches in code.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2023-03-09T19:19:51.693Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":39,"readers_count":38,"score":17.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":429595,"topic_slug":"limit-sensor-crashing-code","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":55902,"username":"vickitine","name":"Victoria","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/vickitine/{size}/180654_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38592,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"FRC 4681 Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/limit-sensor-crashing-code/429595/4","custom_user_title":"FRC 4681 Programming Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3161098,"name":"Victoria","username":"vickitine","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/vickitine/{size}/180654_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-09T19:29:56.768Z","cooked":"<p>We just switched it to the DIO port now, we still get the same issue as before. In the code we are supposed to be putting in one limit sensor and 1 through bore encoder. Could we be accidently putting it in twice?</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2023-03-09T19:29:56.768Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":11.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":429595,"topic_slug":"limit-sensor-crashing-code","display_username":"Victoria","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":38592,"username":"cmarley","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/cmarley/{size}/121111_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":55902,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/limit-sensor-crashing-code/429595/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3161113,"name":"Fletch","username":"Fletch1373","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-09T19:43:13.580Z","cooked":"<p>Youre passing the limit switch port number into the constructor then using it to create a DigitalInput object, while ALSO directly creating a DigitalInput object using a hardcoded port of 1 as a class member variable.  You can’t create multiple of the same object using the same port number anywhere in your code, which is why your code is crashing.</p>
<p>If you only have 1 physical limit switch, then remove one of the two DigitalInput objects from your subsystem.  If you have 2, then change the port number for one (and standardize around a single mechanism for instantiating the object. Either pass it into the constructor, or initialize it directly in the class, not both).  If one is supposed to be a ThroughBore Encoder, then you need to reference the REV docs and fix that.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2023-03-09T19:43:13.580Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":28,"readers_count":27,"score":45.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":429595,"topic_slug":"limit-sensor-crashing-code","display_username":"Fletch","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":55902,"username":"vickitine","name":"Victoria","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/vickitine/{size}/180654_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":9105,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades"},"post_url":"/t/limit-sensor-crashing-code/429595/6","custom_user_title":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3161194,"name":"Victoria","username":"vickitine","avatar_template